We arrived at Ciampino Airport and took the shuttle bus to termini station (6 euro each).	Also has excellent access to public transportation with a bus stop nearby and a bus depot a short walk away at Piazza San Silvestro.	We didn´t use the parking but were offered to.	We could walk to all the sights of Rome within 30 minutes, and we never needed to catch a taxi or a bus.	There is a good bus connection at the hub at Piazza San Silvestre about a 5-minute walk from the hotel.	We flew to Rome through the snowstorm in Paris and our bags were subsequently lost by Air France.	We did get a taxi to/from the hotel for ease.